task.summary: Edited update_ship_controls for better ship rotation. Dampening implemented

Edited gameplay.py. Mostly fixed turret target seeking. Updated and improved visuals.
**BUG**: Turret heading/slope is calculated incorrectly. Will fix in next commit

Expanded test_gameplay.py to simulate three ships.
Fixed turret rotation/enemy ship spotting.
**BUG** Math domain error with acos. To be fixed in future commit

Added user interactivity, user can position ship with cursor.
Modified ship and turret targeting.
**GLITCH** Sometimes turrets point in the wrong direction or doesn't completely focus at the target

Edited graphics,py, vmath.py, gameplay.py, and test_gameplay.py
- Improved more complex visuals - Turrets now focus on target independently based off of real turret position, not ship position - Fixed many targeting bugs
**GLITCH**: If ship goes too close to another ship, its turrets will not fully track the target.

Edited graphics.py, vmath.py, gameplay.py, and test_gameplay.py
Fixed all known targeting bugs; turrets and ship now track target completely.
Added test ship engine and fixed velocity and propulsion bugs. Currently no further problems identified, though more thorough tests are needed.
TODO: Ship velocity visual, thrust/fire graphics, shooting

Edited gameplay.py, test_gameplay.py
(Re)fixed all targeting bugs. Corrected typo that prevented ship from tracking target after reaching a certain distance away from it.
Propulsion is mostly fixed, but cruising speed is ignored.

Edited vmath.py, gameplay.py, test_gameplay.py
Tried to clamp velocity within cruising speed, but velocity will slowly and steadily surpass it.
Added visuals depicting ship velocity and cruising velocity.
Next commit will change ship spotting to have it control its own velocity more, as well as possible optimizations
